# Goal Description

The goal is to create a clean, single-entry-point Python script (`run_live_demo.py`) that boots up the entire Lineage Engine application (Databases, backend API, & frontend UI), automatically launches the browser to view the dashboard, and kicks off a "live" pipeline simulator. This simulator will execute pipeline jobs (from the Jaffle Shop model) at realistic intervals to demonstrate how the dashboard reacts and populates events in real time. We will also address the educational request by providing a document explaining process orchestration.

## User Review Required

I have designed a Python orchestrator structure below and propose making it simulate the Jaffle Shop pipeline by inserting events slowly over time so you can actually "watch" the DAG grow on the screen. Please review this.

